The two payments listed above were for the completion of services as per the written agreement
between Culpepper Security Services, Inc. and Modern Management, Inc. (enclosed)
I would like to thank you on behalt of our firm for selecting Modern Management, Inc. to
provide consulting services to your organization. We will de our very best to earn the
confidence placed in us, although we are not usually in a position to guarantee any specific
results. We are prepared to provide a wide variety of services to advise and consult with you
on the development of employee relations skills. particularly in the area of communication
between management and employees. In order to avoid any misunderstanding, this letter will
describe the basis of our consulting services in this matter and in any other matters in which
you may in the future ask us to be of service to you.
It is agreed that Modern Management personnel will first meet with management to ascertain
their goals. Modern Management personnel will then conduct a series of group and individual
meetings with management and supervisors to ascertain both the source of weaknesses in
present communication lines and possible areas of training and advice as to how the
supervisors can improve those lines of communication and their methods of problem solving
and motivation. Based on the discussions with the supervisors, Modern Management
personnel will then advise and make suggestions to management as to how the desired goals
can be achieved. The decision as to whether the suggestions and advice will be followed rests
solely with Culpepper & Associates Security Services. Inc.
II is also agreed that Modern Management will advise and consult with management on the
subject of union activity and campaign strategy. Modern Management personnel will provide
guidance to management to avoid engaging in conduct which could be construed as a violation
of the law. and will outline permissible communication conduct. In addition, if desirous.
Modern Management personnel will review your drafts of communication letters and speeches.
offer suggestions for improvement. if needed. and work with Culpepper & Associates Security
Services. Inc. is legal coansel with respect to other communication matters.
It should be understood. however, that Modern Management's advisory and consulting
functions as detailed above will be limited to meetings with the managerial staft only; there
will be no contact between Modern Management personnel and non-supervisory employees.
11 is further understeod that Modern Management's functions are limited to advice and
consultation. Culpepper & Associates Security Services. Inc. is not obligated to accept the
advice and suggestions of Modern Management. All decision making authority rests with
We will keep you reasonably informed on the status of your matters and will promptly comply
with your requests for information. You should identify the persons. if any. other than
yourself. with whom we are authorized to communicate regarding your matters. Other
consultants or support personnel may be assigned. as appears appropriate. to optimize the
effectiveness and economy of our services.
Our billing practice is to invoice clients monthly for the services rendered and any costs
advanced or incurred during the month. Fees for services will usually be determined based
upen the amount of time expended for the matter. Each consultant and support consultant in
our firm is assigned a minimum hourly rate that is appropriate for his OF her services. Al this
time, our hourly rates range from $150 - $350. Gary Riseling billing rate is $250 per hour.
These hourly rates are subject to periodic adjustment and our bills will reflect the rates in
effect on the date that services are rendered. Our detailed monthly invoices will provide the
names of the consultant performing the services.
Our monthly bills also reflect "costs. that is. ut-of-pocket advances or special internal costs
incurred on your behalf. for which we are to be reimbursed. These expenses will be listed
separately on your monthly billing and include trave), lodging and meals. En addition. there is
an overail communication/administration charge of 4 percent of the professional fees.
Absent our written agreement to the contrary. our invoices are payable on receipt. and in any
event. payment of all invoices is due within thirty (30) days of the date of the invoice. It' no
comments or inquiries about a bill are received within 30 days of the invoice date, we can
assume that you have reviewed the bill and found it acceptable.
We believe it is both ethically appropriate and business-like to advisé clients in advance that
they always have the right to terminate our professional services and to do so with or without
reason. That absolute legal right to terminate does not affect our right to compensation for
services already rendered and to be reimbursed for costs expended. nor will- il relieve you et
the obligation to pay collection expenses associated with unpaid invoices.
